  • Classes in MenueSystem used by MenueSystem 
    Class and Description
    Button
    Maintains a multiState button that uses the size of its background rectangle to determine if the mouse is placed over it
    Button.transitionState 
    Label
    Will maintain a label which can display a string of text at a given position
    Panel
    Maintains a panel which draws maintains a simple background image and can also contain a series of sub panels with this one Note this panel does not force any of the sub panels to actually reside inside this panel.
    Panel.PanelState
    Used to mark what operating mode this panel is in IDLE: all Sub panels are updated normally.
